===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|i}} – hill. Earlier form closer to {{zh-l|*丠}}, as in {{och-l|虛}}. Compare {{zh-l|*山}}. Unrelated to [[兵]] and [[斤]].

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=丠,㐀,𡊣,㘳,坵,𠀈,𠀉,𠀌}}
{{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} relates this word to {{zh-l|墟}} "ruin-mound". However, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} disagrees.

Schuessler considers two homophones [[丘]], "hill, mound" and [[丘]] "village, district" to be the same word as settlements were often built on elevated grounds (for a parallel see {{zh-l|京}}) and traces this word's etymology to {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*rwəʔ||village}}; within Sinitic, {{och-l|丘}} is cognate with {{och-l|里}} "village" and {{och-l|街}} "road crossing, street"; outsides Sinitic, cognate with {{cog|lus|khua||village}}, {{cog|cnh|khûa||village, cosmos}}, and {{cog|my|ရွာ||village}} (STEDT).

